{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.13",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
    "chapterNumber": 13,
    "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 13",
    "summary": "Source text for 1 Corinthians 13 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.13.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 13:1",
      "text": "If I speak in the tongues of men and of angels, but have not love, I am a noisy gong or a clanging cymbal.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.13.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 13:2",
      "text": "And if I have prophetic powers, and understand all mysteries and all knowledge, and if I have all faith, so as to remove mountains, but have not love, I am nothing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.13.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 13:3",
      "text": "If I give away all I have, and if I deliver my body to be burned, but have not love, I gain nothing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.13.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 13:4",
      "text": "Love is patient and kind; love is not jealous or boastful;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.13.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 13:5",
      "text": "it is not arrogant or rude. Love does not insist on its own way; it is not irritable or resentful;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.13.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 13:6",
      "text": "it does not rejoice at wrong, but rejoices in the right.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.13.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 13:7",
      "text": "Love bears all things, believes all things, hopes all things, endures all things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.13.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 13:8",
      "text": "Love never ends; as for prophecies, they will pass away; as for tongues, they will cease; as for knowledge, it will pass away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.13.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 13:9",
      "text": "For our knowledge is imperfect and our prophecy is imperfect;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.13.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 13:10",
      "text": "but when the perfect comes, the imperfect will pass away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.13.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 13:11",
      "text": "When I was a child, I spoke like a child, I thought like a child, I reasoned like a child; when I became a man, I gave up childish ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.13.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 13:12",
      "text": "For now we see in a mirror dimly, but then face to face. Now I know in part; then I shall understand fully, even as I have been fully understood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.13.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 13:13",
      "text": "So faith, hope, love abide, these three; but the greatest of these is love.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
